result.execSummary:
The defendant Tony Jamar Criss was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Disorderly Conduct, a class B misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 947.01(1).
  • Bail Jumping-Misdemeanor, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.49(1)(a).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Case called at 10:11 AM.
Defendant Tony Jamar Criss in court with attorney Jane Ellen Bucher.  Defendant Tony Jamar Criss in custody.  Katherine M. Findley appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Matter is resolved.
Defendant withdrawals plea of "NOT GUILTY and enters a plea of "NO CONTEST" to Counts 1 & 2.
Factual basis is found.
Court questions defendant and counsel re: plea and waiver of rights.
Court finds plea and waiver is made freely, knowingly & intelligently.
Court accepts plea and finds the defendant "GUILTY" to Counts 1 & 2.
State moves for joint recommendation of the parties, attorney Bucher concurs with the state.
Court grants motion of the parties 
Count 1 - 30 days in the Lafayette County Jail with Huber privileges, consecutive with the jail time ordered in Count 2 of Lafayette County Case No. 16-CM-97.
Count 2 - 30 days in the Lafayette County Jail with Huber privileges, concurrent with C1, and also the jail time ordered in Count 2 of Lafayette County Case No. 16-CM-97.
Costs (DNA Surcharge is waived on both counts).
Sentence may be served in Grant County.
Plea/sentencing hearing on November 21, 2016 at 10:00 am.
